# Objective Form UX Standards

- Every form field must have a visible heading label above the input (do not rely on placeholder only).
- Use the existing screen pattern for labels and spacing:
  - Label: `text-xs text-zinc-600`
  - Input spacing: `mt-1 w-full ...`
- Primary save buttons (for example `Objective speichern`) stay disabled until all required fields are valid.
- Keep HTML `required` attributes and add client-side submit gating (`canSubmit`) for immediate UX feedback.
- Numeric score fields must define `min` and `max` and clamp typed values to valid bounds.
- For `importance_score`, enforce strict range `1..5`.
